The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of seven (7) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision, on each count, concurrent.
The Court finds her eligible for the Substance Abuse Program, but not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs including $300.00 to Metro Drug Unit;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) no contact with any known drug dealers or users.
Defendant has credit for 1 day.
Minutes.
